        <exercise xml:id="auto_phixkou5">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_lvnm4h1o">
                    The displacement-time graph below shows a car accelerating smoothly from rest.
                </p>
                <image width="60%">
                    <latex-image label = "interpretation 2">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                            % Draw fine grid (10x smaller squares)
                            \draw[gray!30, very thin, step=0.1] (0,0) grid (6,5);

                            % Draw main grid (original)
                            \draw[gray!70, thin, step=1] (0,0) grid (6,5);

                            % Axes
                            \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (6,0);
                            \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (0,5.5);
                            \node[above, rotate=90] at (-0.8,2) {\textbf {Displacement (m)}};
                            \node[below] at (4.5,-0.4) {\textbf{Time (s)}};

                            % Y-axis labels (same format as X-axis)
                            \foreach \y in {1,2,3,4,5}
                                \draw (-0.2,\y) -- (0.2,\y) node[left=6pt] {\y};

                            % X-axis labels
                            \foreach \x in {1,2,3,4,5}
                                \draw (\x,-0.2) -- (\x,0.2) node[below=6pt] {\x};

                            % Graph Title
                            \node[above] at (2,5.5) {\textbf{Displacement-Time Graph for Uniform Acceleration (1 m/s²)}};

                            % Parabolic Curve for s = (1/2)at², where a = 1 m/s²
                            \draw[thick,blue] plot[smooth] coordinates {
                                (0,0) 
                                (1,0.5) 
                                (2,2.0) 
                                (3,4.5) 
                            };

                            % Mark Displacement at t=3s
                            \draw[dashed] (3,4.5) -- (3,-0.5) node[below] {$3s$};
                            \draw[dashed] (3,4.5) -- (-0.5,4.5) node[left] {$4.5m$};
                                                
                            % Point at (3s, 4.5m)
                            \fill (3,4.5) circle (3pt);
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
                <p xml:id="auto_c1ozw7wa">
                    Use the graph to answer the following questions:
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_soec1dqd">
                    <ol xml:id="auto_p5s74vb0" marker="a)">
                        <li xml:id="auto_br5o0xid">
                            <p xml:id="auto_j13zkexg">
                                Describe the motion of the car as shown in the graph. Is the velocity constant, increasing, or decreasing? Justify your answer.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_vbqpt0qj">
                            <p xml:id="auto_a978x195">
                                What does the y-intercept of the graph represent?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_i0iezunx">
                            <p xml:id="auto_ihx859oe">
                                Calculate the average velocity of the object between <m>\textbf{t}</m> = <m>0 \textbf{ s}</m> and <m>\textbf{t}</m> = <m>3 \textbf{ s}</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_cqs8wck9">
                    <ol xml:id="auto_x1wnqyn0" marker="a)">
                        <li xml:id="auto_5ff47srm" >
                            <p xml:id="auto_qsmrd59s" >
                                The graph shows a curved line that gets steeper over time, indicating that the car's velocity is increasing. This means the car is accelerating.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_14s3nnr8">
                            <p xml:id="auto_om8wutkb">
                                The y-intercept of the graph represents the initial displacement of the car at time <m>t</m> = <m>0 \,\text{s}</m>. In this case, it is <m>0 \,\text{m}</m>, indicating that the car started from rest at the origin.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_olwuacoz">
                            <p xml:id="auto_etsxydrr">
                                The average velocity can be calculated using the formula:
                            </p>
                            <p xml:id="auto_nqp0vsj9">
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>\text{Average Velocity} = \frac{\text{Total Displacement}}{\text{Total Time}}</mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \frac{4.5 \,\text{m} - 0 \,\text{m}}{3 \,\text{s} - 0 \,\text{s}}</mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \frac{4.5 \,\text{m}}{3 \,\text{s}} = 1.5 \,\text{m/s}</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p xml:id="auto_177fgzkd">
